   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>In the firste ingresse of this discourse before I descended to any particuler Treatise, I preconceiued, that these my sclender Meditations, shoulde come to the vew and censure of three sortes of persons; Catholicks, protes<g ref="char:EOLunhyphen"/>tantes, &amp; demi-catholickes, or ca<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tholique-like protestantes; or exter<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>nall protestantes, &amp; internall catho<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>likes: some call them Churche-pa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>pistes, others Scis matiques, whose mindes I thoughte good to prepare in particuler before I went any further.</p>
</div>
